<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880912-0109 </DOCNO><HL> Singer Co. Receives Total of $56.4 Million In Contracts for Navy </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AN LTV HRS MHS TXN WX GE NOC GD </CO><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Singer Co. received $56.4 million in Navy contracts for helicopter simulators and computer parts.    Amoco Oil Co., a unit of Amoco Corp., won a $49.1 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel.    LTV Corp. was awarded a $45.5 million Army contract for missile-warhead development.    Harris Corp. was issued $32.9 million in Navy and Air Force contracts for computer-training equipment, satellite parts and aircraft-test systems.    Marriott Corp. got a $30.3 million Air Force contract for a hospital-management system.    Texas Instruments Inc. was awarded a $24.2 million Air Force contract for conventional-weapons studies.    Dyncorp Support Services Inc., a unit of Dyncorp., won an $18.1 million Navy contract for support of the Pacific Fleet hospital office.    Westinghouse Electric Corp. was issued $14.1 million in Navy and Air Force contracts for nuclear-propulsion development and satellite equipment.    General Electric Co. got $13 million in Navy and Air Force contracts for nuclear-propulsion studies and flight-test support.    Northrop Corp. won a $12 million Air Force contract for aircraft maintenance.    General Dynamics Corp. received a $10.1 million Air Force contract for F-16 aircraft support. </TEXT></DOC>